header.gameNote: SOUTH PADRE ISLAND INVITATIONAL AT SOUTH PADRE ISLAND TX

article.headline: Sam Houston State 62, Delaware State 55
article.story: SOUTH PADRE ISLAND, Texas (AP) -- Aaron Wade scored 19 points and Sam Houston State beat Delaware State 62-55 Saturday in the South Padre Island Invitational consolation championship. Ryan Bright had 12 points and nine rebounds for the Bearkats (4-2). JeJuan Plair added 10 points. Darrin Shine led Delaware State (2-5) with 13 points. The Bearkats took advantage of Delaware State's 29 percent shooting in the first half to build a 19-point lead.
